[
  {
    "id": "fleetwringer",
    "type": "tab",
    "label": "MAVLink SITL - Multi-Drone Fleet Wringer",
    "disabled": false,
    "info": "Discover, arm, take off, and reshuffle a whole fleet of SITL drones on ONE routed UDP connection (14550) — and prove they never collide.\n\n## Start the fleet\n\nRun a virtual multi-drone SITL (no PX4/ArduPilot needed) from the source repo:\n\n    ./test/sitl/start-fleet.sh            # 3 drones, sysid 1..3 -> 127.0.0.1:14550\n\nor one container per drone with distinct sysids:\n\n    docker compose -f test/sitl/docker-compose.yml up --build\n\nThese are development helpers and are NOT shipped in the npm package: https://github.com/cmc0619/node-red-contrib-mavlink-ai/tree/main/test/sitl\n\nA real PX4/ArduPilot multi-vehicle SITL streaming to UDP 14550 works too.\n\n## The wringer\n\n1. Deploy. The Swarm registry lists the drones as their HEARTBEATs arrive; the Separation monitor tracks the closest pair live.\n2. Inject **1 Arm all**, then **2 Take off (layered)** — each drone climbs to its own altitude layer (10 m apart) so a later horizontal reshuffle can cross paths safely.\n3. Inject **3 Reposition (reversed line)** to swap the formation end-for-end. Paths cross, but the altitude layering keeps every pair apart — watch the Separation monitor stay green.\n\nThe **Preview (dry-run)** inject shows exactly what the reposition would send without touching a vehicle."
  },
